    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102653</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>A batch of orange paint is made with 4 cups of yellow paint and 6 cups of red paint.</p>

<ol>
	<li>Draw a diagram representing one batch of orange paint.</li>
	<li>How many cups of yellow and red paint are needed for half a batch?</li>
	<li>How many cups of yellow and red paint are needed for three batches?</li>
	<li>Explain why all of these mixtures of paint will make the same shade of orange.</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>Answers vary. Sample response:
	<p><img class="h-max-height--5-lines" src="/image_files/30674.png" /></p>
	</li>
	<li>2 cups yellow and 3 cups red</li>
	<li>12 cups yellow and 18 cups red</li>
	<li>They are all different numbers of batches of the same paint recipe. The ratios of yellow paint to red paint in these mixtures are equivalent.</li>
</ol>
</div>
